        <p style="text-align: center; font-size: 0.85rem; color: #666; font-style: italic; margin-top: -8px; margin-bottom: 20px;"><strong>Christian Pulisic</strong>, the star of the United States, in action. His performance will be crucial in the decisive match against Bosnia-Herzegovina at <strong>MetLife Stadium</strong>.</p>

        <div class="content">
            <p style="text-align: justify;">The <strong>MetLife Stadium</strong> in <strong>New York / New Jersey</strong> is set to host one of the most anticipated and high-stakes matches of the tournament. On <strong>July 2, 2026</strong>, at <strong>02:00 CEST</strong>, the <strong>United States</strong> will face <strong>Bosnia and Herzegovina</strong> in a do-or-die encounter for the home team. After a sluggish start to the tournament, <strong>Mauricio Pochettino's</strong> men are <strong>obligated to win</strong> to keep their qualification hopes alive, relying on the dynamism of their star, <strong>Christian Pulisic</strong>.</p><p style="text-align: justify;">On the other side, <strong>Bosnia and Herzegovina</strong> present themselves as a solid and tricky opponent, known for their defensive organization and lethal counter-attacks, orchestrated by the charisma and experience of veteran <strong>Edin Dzeko</strong>. It will be a tactical and physical battle where every mistake could prove fatal.</p><h3>Match Data and Context</h3><p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Teams:</strong> United States vs. Bosnia and Herzegovina</p><p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Date:</strong> July 2, 2026</p><p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Time:</strong> 02:00 CEST</p><p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Stadium:</strong> <strong>MetLife Stadium</strong>, New York / New Jersey</p><p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Context:</strong> Decisive night match. The <strong>USA</strong> must win at home after a slow start. <strong>Bosnia and Herzegovina</strong>, with their low-block back three defense, will aim to exploit <strong>counter-attacks</strong> led by <strong>Edin Dzeko</strong>.</p><h3>Tactical Keys</h3><p style="text-align: justify;">For the <strong>United States</strong>, <strong>Pochettino's</strong> strategy will focus on breaking down the compact Bosnian defensive block. <strong>Christian Pulisic's</strong> ability to create numerical superiority, both with his bursts of speed and his vision, will be crucial in refining offensive plays. Patience in building up play and precision in passing will be essential to avoid leaving themselves exposed to the opponent's lethal counter-attacks.</p><p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Bosnia and Herzegovina</strong>, true to their setup, will line up with a <strong>three-man</strong> defense, aiming to close every gap and stifle American initiatives in midfield. <strong>Edin Dzeko's</strong> role will be vital not only as a finisher but also as a focal point to bring the team up the pitch and relieve defensive pressure, exploiting any slight lapse in concentration to strike on the <strong>counter-attack</strong>.</p><h3>Probable Lineups</h3><p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>United States (4-3-3)</strong></p><p class="coach">Head Coach: <strong>Mauricio Pochettino</strong></p><p style="text-align: justify;">Goalkeeper; Right-Back, Centre-Back 1, Centre-Back 2, Left-Back; Midfielder 1, Midfielder 2, Midfielder 3; Right Winger, Striker, <strong>Christian Pulisic</strong>.</p><p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>Bosnia and Herzegovina (3-5-2)</strong></p><p class="coach">Head Coach: [Bosnia Coach]</p><p style="text-align: justify;">Goalkeeper; Centre-Back 1, Centre-Back 2, Centre-Back 3; Right Wing-Back, Midfielder 1, Midfielder 2, Midfielder 3, Left Wing-Back; Forward 1, <strong>Edin Dzeko</strong>.</p>
